ional military park. </strong>(sen. (candidate full), "(candidate last), frist win $1.5 million for shiloh national military park," press release, 11/22/99) </p><p><strong> $3 million for fire ant quarantine. </strong>(sen. (candidate full), "(candidate last), frist secure $3 million for fire ant quarantine," press release, 7/29/02) </p><p><strong> $651,000 for two bridges in hatchie national wildlife refuge in west tennessee. </strong>(sen. (candidate full), "(candidate last), frist secure $651,000 for haywood county bridges," press release, 11/22/99) </p><p><strong> $1.5 million for "five bridges and water control structures" in cross creeks national wildlife refuge.</strong> (sen. (candidate full), "(candidate last), frist secure $1.5 million for stewart county bridges," press release, 11/22/99)</p></span>



